it is timely that now we have an open discussion about what consent is and more importantly, what it is not. surely, it is not a justification for rape. let's discuss further in our event below:

ticket: 30k

warning: the film is rated r and includes some rape and gore scenes.

discussion will be held in bahasa indonesia.

online ticket can be purchased at livelife:

sources connected to the embattled singer tell us the panic attacks started in the days leading up to "surviving r. kelly" airing last week. the firestorm that erupted after it aired is affecting him, too, because we're told they've continued with one attack being so serious, he sought treatment at a hospital.

we're told kelly's aware the pendulum isn't swinging his way right now in the court of public opinion.
as for hisÂ birthday celebration wednesday night ... we're told kelly's looking for reasons to get out of his house. quite frankly, we're told he still believes he's done nothing wrong andÂ doesn't want to seem like he's hiding.
his dwindling number of supporters -- many of whom cheered him in the nightclub -- might think he's unfazed by the controversy. truth is, the public outrage -- evenÂ from kelly's own bloodÂ -- is getting to him.

first, the book gives you information. information on power structure, gender bias, the wage gap, rape culture, lack of women in government. then it helps you find your cause. once you're ready to go, this book walks you through everything from fundraising, lobbying and marketing to running an effective meeting and creating the perfect phonebank.  finding yourself up against people who disagree?  this book will help you handle that. starting to burn out? flip to chapter 8.

you could literally use this book to organize the women's march (seriously, i think you could), but you can also use it to make change in smaller ways. the book is inclusive, informational, inspirational and, most importantly, instructional. it is super.

text:
a woman described as â€œan online troll of the worst kindâ€ has been jailed for falsely accusing primary school parents of satanic abuse and cannibalism.

sabine mcneill, 74, led a campaign to uncover baseless devil worship and child abuse at a primary school in hampstead, northwest london.

she harassed four mothers, who cannot be named, claiming they were members of a cult who cooked and ate babies. she also made allegations of murder, southwark crown court heard.

the court heard how mcneill repeatedly harassed her victims from 2014 until earlier this year. prosecutor miranda moore said the pensioner had published â€˜scandalous satanic child abuse accusationsâ€™ and encouraged people â€˜to take direct action against the children of these womenâ€™. in her words, mcneill said the women would: â€˜drink the blood of babies and then dance around wearing the skulls on parts of their bodies. â€˜they would put them to sleep by injecting them, slit their throats, cook the babies and eat them. â€˜the ritual is performed on an upstairs room in mcdonaldâ€™s on mondays and fridays. sacrifice, blood drinking and babiesâ€™ flesh eating occurs on saturdays. â€˜the children are frequently injected and put to sleep, apparently the school nurse is the one who does the injections.â€™ mcneill claimed up to 18 teachers from the primary school were also involved in abusing children. she wrote that members of the cult carried out the acts in secret rooms in a hampstead church.

mcneill, from camden, north london, was convicted of four counts of harassment and six counts of breaching a restraining order.

miranda moore, prosecuting, had told the jury she was â€œan online troll of the worst kind, making the lives of innocent families a miseryâ€.

text:
r. kellyâ€™s attorney, steve greenberg, confirmed friday morning that his client married the late star aaliyah in 1994 when she was 15 years old and kelly was 27. 
the lawyer said aaliyah lied about her age, and he defended the union by noting that â€œelvis was married to priscilla,â€ referring to the king of rock â€˜nâ€™ roll dating priscilla when she was 14 and then marrying her when she was 21.

greenberg was speaking on abcâ€™s â€œgood morning americaâ€ in response to several sexual abuse allegations against kelly, which emerged through a lifetime docuseries, â€œsurviving r. kelly.â€ after greenberg asserted that kelly â€œabsolutelyâ€ denies ever being with any underage girls, reporter linsey davis asked, â€œwas he married to aaliyah when she was 15?â€ â€œhe was married to her when she was 15. elvis was married to priscilla,â€ greenberg replied, and went on to insist that kelly had â€œno ideaâ€ of aaliyahâ€™s age.

the daily mail noted that kelly met aaliyah when she was 12, produced her record, â€œage ainâ€™t nothinâ€™ but a number,â€ and sat with her during a 1994 bet interview where her age was repeatedly cited as 14.

kellyâ€™s attorney is trying to run damage control over the six-part series on kelly, which ran last week. after its airing, multiple investigations were reportedly launched by authorities, and criminal charges against the singer have already been threatened. get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com what do you guys think? #aaliyah #aaliyahdanahaughton #aaliyahformac #aaliyahhaughton #oneinamillion #ripaaliyah #rkelly #survivingrkelly #robertkelly #muterkelly #ageaintnothingbutanumber #trappedinthecloset #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog

this is the first book of itâ€™s kind. the black manâ€™s bible details a young black males struggles with the world, religions, drugs, crime, money and sex. throughout his life he studies advanced scholarly material which changes his view of the world over and over again as he matures. he battles health issues after he goes through a traumatic experience with the delivery of his first child. so he delivered his second son at home. the video of the home delivery can be seen at theblackmansbible.com. in the book he details how he finds himself in history repeatedly in different times periods. he also gives vivid descriptions of his experiences with love and women. then, after becoming an online entrepreneur, he travels to germany and china for free. he has struggles with finding a career and ends up becoming an author. he covers many subjects that are not popular to the modern day world. he has compiled a multitude of experiences that are dissected through the abstract different types of black males. this is the book of the century. the true guide for black males lost in the western world.

text:
â€œgirls onlyâ€
@behrpaint on birchwood panel
10â€ x 10â€
.
this is the last of the satirical and raw series, which is a symbolic placeholder for the next male portrait that is brought to the spotlight for his misdeeds. in this current political climate, we see countless examples of men abusing their power against women, men trying to role back womenâ€™s rights, sexist and misogynist language being accepted and perpetuated. i had been reflecting upon our current political climate, the â€œme tooâ€ movement, and feminist theory, when conceptualizing this body of work. i found that @behrpaint â€˜s blues and greens are often labeled after natural elements such as sky, rainwater, artichoke, thundercloud, forest green, or sage. then the reds and pinks are centralized around the female trope and gender roles that are exacerbated in our society such as â€œhot gossip, drama queen, girls only, flirt alert, no more drama, diva glam, etc.â€. my irritation with this companyâ€™s branding (which is also prevalent in the naming of nail polish) and my anger at the revelations we are now seeing so frequently thanks to the â€œme tooâ€ movement was a driving factor in this project. i combined the names that @behrpaint uses to label their colors with portraits of men that have abused their power, taken advantage of women, have made misogynst/sexist remarks, or have been accused of corruption. look forward to photographing the final project of 12 portraits all installed together as one piece.Â Â be on the look out! .
.
.
.
.

text:
i did something scary today.
-
i finally spoke up on an issue i have been ruminating on for months: sexual harassment. specifically in the wedding industry. in my stories now is a 14 minute video talking about my experiences with this dark issue and how iâ€™m going to handle it moving forward. i have been working for months on how to say what i want to say. how to convey how serious it is. but how not to offend or target. how to be strong. but understanding. iâ€™ve been a wreck leading up to it. it was hard to do. iâ€™m feeling emotionally drained now. but iâ€™m glad i finally did it. you may not be the type to watch a long video and thatâ€™s okay but just know this: if you have been or are being sexually harassed or abused (wedding industry aside), itâ€™s not your fault. itâ€™s never your fault. you matter enough to speak up. you are more than that incident or situation. you are not alone. to those of you who have never had to deal with these issues: wake up. open your eyes. advocate. look out for your fellow man. speak up for your fellow woman. sometimes we cannot prevent these wrong and evil things from happening. but we can stand up and speak out when they do. we can listen. instead of being a bystander, letâ€™s be a friend. instead of being an accuser, letâ€™s work on becoming an ally.
-
okay. go watch my story. or donâ€™t. either way, thank you for even reading this. have an awesome day, hug someone and drink more water. ğŸ‘ŠğŸ½
-

r. kellyâ€™s studio in the westside of chicago will be subject a search on jan. 16th. 
it looks like years of alleged sex crimes are finally beginning to catch up to r. kelly. surviving r. kelly put a massive spotlight on allegations of sexual abuse over the years which prompted authorities to intervene. while chicago police decided not to conduct an investigation immediately after the docuseries aired, they did ask for eyewitnesses and victims to come forward with stories. now, chicago police have ordered the singer to allow them to inspect his studio in the westside of chicago which is also where he reportedly housed his alleged sex slaves.

according to chicago sun-times, a chicago judge honored the cityâ€™s request to search kellzâ€™ recording studio. the inspection is set to take place on jan. 16th at noon. kellyâ€™s lawyer initially asked the judge to give them 30 days to comply which clearly wasnâ€™t granted. the judgeâ€™s decision comes just a day after the city filed an emergency motion asking for access to the building. the cityâ€™s attorney believe the building is being used illegally as a recording studio and living space even though the property is only being zoned for industrial use. â€œupon information and belief it is being used as a residence and artist workspace â€” specifically as a recording studio in violation of the zoning law,â€ city attorneys said.

the lawyer for the property managers claimed that they didnâ€™t have access to the building. 
the cityâ€™s request to inspect the studio also comes a few days after another judge ordered for kellyâ€™s eviction from the unit. midwest commercial funding took a win in the case after they claimed the singer owned them $80k in back rent.  get the full details at www.itskenbarbie.com #rkelly #robertkelly #survivingrkelly #trappedinthecloset #muterkelly #lifetime #lifetimetv #ibelieveicanfly #metoo #entertainment #entertainmentnews #entertainmentblog #gossip

text:
one of our phenomenal acts - @likwuid with r.o.t.i. from likwuid: â€œ2018 was a breakthrough for women across the globe...women in saudi arabia were exercising and driving in public, women in america were yelling metoo, while women in france yelled #noustoutes, women took office, lead marches and grabbed back. furthermore, women in hollywood decided to check the film industry, and now in 2019, black women are in an intersectional war with misogyny in the music industry. i think we are seeing that the momentum from women reclaiming our voice has only begun.

being a part of this event is an honor and a privilege, because planned parenthood is a reminder to everyone that women are fully capable and informed about making decisions concerning our own bodies. 
i think events such as this one are important for visibility and for educating those that aren't aware of their options and alternatives. sometimes we take information for granted and not everyone is in a financial, mental or social space to be aware. so i think it's important to have reminders that are informative but also entertaining. (i'd like to think of events with a purpose as "aspirin in the applesauce".)â€

text: over the christmas window a group of us had a very loud discussion on linkedin about domestic and family violence support services shutting over the christmas window. it grew from there. this was not about front line workers needing a break. they certainly do. but it was not ok to simply tell those in danger these are holiday emergency services when some might need a great deal more support. this was about what is going on in australia with regard to violence and it cannot continue. and so we decided to collectively come together to use our voice to see how as a community we can bring about change. itâ€™s really been humbling to watch people power in action, waging peace. we have filmmakers, lawyers, teachers, psychologists, academics, mums, dads, victims and survivors all coming together to discuss the issue. many are travelling from all over australia just to attend. it intersects, #metoo #genderequity #endviolenceagainstwomen and more. if youâ€™d like to add your voice please dm. space is likely to be an issue so you must rsvp. we actually might need to move location as a result. btw - if you are on linkedin please come join the discussion there too. #safety #timesup #wagepeace #faith ps: this is a discussion forum where a positive action plan will be discussed. in other words, what can we do to help? #hillsongsisterhoodaustralia

this is the first book of itâ€™s kind. the black manâ€™s bible details a young black males struggles with the world, religions, drugs, crime, money and sex. throughout his life he studies advanced scholarly material which changes his view of the world over and over again as he matures. he battles health issues after he goes through a traumatic experience with the delivery of his first child. so he delivered his second son at home. the video of the home delivery can be seen at theblackmansbible.com. in the book he details how he finds himself in history repeatedly in different times periods. he also gives vivid descriptions of his experiences with love and women. then, after becoming an online entrepreneur, he travels to germany and china for free. he has struggles with finding a career and ends up becoming an author. he covers many subjects that are not popular to the modern day world. he has compiled a multitude of experiences that are dissected through the abstract different types of black males. this is the book of the century. the true guide for black males lost in the western world.

text:
about the rape of lucretia by benjamin britten, tacoma operaâ€™s upcoming show:

the rape of lucretia is a very different kind of opera.

it's a serious and tragic chamber opera set in ancient roman times,
based on a true story that is not only timeless, but is even more timely
and current today in 2018, during the #metoo movement.

benjamin britten tells this story with such compassion and understanding for the characters, that audiences are drawn into the story in a way that moves one to the core of one's being.

the rape of lucretia is not at all graphic or gory by today's
hollywood standards, but rather, it is a thought provoking,
psychological retelling of a true and tragic story.

this an opera you won't have many opportunities to see in the future,
so experience it now!

text:
so excited to announce that #allthewomeninmyfamilysing contibutor @writenowladybug's book - 'write this second: a poetic memoir" comes out at the end of this month. pre-order today! link in bio.

kira lynne allenâ€™s poetic memoir write this second is both a truth-telling, visceral story of survival and an urgent, triumphant call to break the silence impacting generations of survivors. it is not a comprehensive rendering of her life, but a focus on lived experiences highlighting societal tides that must turn. the tides of: racism, incest, poverty, rape, addiction, eating disorders, being silenced, domestic violence, suicide and ptsd that have yet to be addressed by #metoo or timeâ€™s up. their deep impact demonstrates how generations of women and children will continue to drown in these tides until we speak to and listen to and believe one another. write this second is one womanâ€™s story of finding voice through recovery and poetry, designed to empower others to find and proclaim their authentic selves.

kira lynne allen is a four time vona voices fellow, a poetry for the people alumna, and a phenomenal workshop facilitator. she is a contributor to all the women in my family sing, tayo literary magazine and endangered species, enduring values. she has more than a dozen poems in anthologies and two self-published chapbooks. her poetic memoir, write this second charts her journey from desecration to divinity; from addict and high school dropout to masterâ€™s degree recipient, poet, performer, collage artist, activist, and community leader. ms. allenâ€™s story is meant to inspire readers to transform their lives by finding and proclaiming their authentic selves, check out http://writethissec.com for more information. kira grew up in the bay area and raised two brave, brilliant resilient daughters in oakland, ca, where she still lives with her partner kat.
#wocauthors #amplifywocvoices #diversespines #poeticmemoir #indiepublisher

i am here to uplift my people. was it easy? not at all. iâ€™ve been told i donâ€™t look native enough. native women donâ€™t look the way i do. iâ€™m not even â€œfitâ€. i am unhealthy looking. iâ€™m just a skinny girl with a cool background. 
guys, this all came from people within the native community. my own people throwing stones at me. when you know who you are you donâ€™t have to be liked. so i kept going and i stand today a motivational speaker. i wanted to make my mark on indian country and show the youth even adults the importance of self development. 
this time last year i was a cashier. i trained people for free between working and going to school. i purchased my personal training studies on a credit card not knowing if iâ€™d even pass the test! science was my weakest subject! there were days iâ€™d sit in my car after closing up the cafe and cry. i cried about self doubts, that my dream is just so far fetched! i hesitated to quit my cafe job to open up my own business. i was so afraid in that very moment but i followed my instinct and quit anyway and it paid off!!! three days after quitting my cashier job i got a call from my tribe the yakama nation to come and host a motivational talk for the tribal school! 
i aiming to teach our girls that they are strong. my message and talks come from my life experiences. i lived on the east coast and faced racism, i am a sexual assault survivor whose trial is in favor to put my abuser behind bars (only 6% of survivors actually win in court and i know i will be one of those) and iâ€™ve been bullied a lot but i never allowed those people to have that power to stop me. 
i have worked with natives across the country showing them the path to new and healthy opportunities. my motto is â€œmake indian country healthy again!â€ i hope this gives someone out there the courage to try again. whatever it is, losing weight, confronting your toxic relationships, going to school, waking up early whatever it is try again and donâ€™t let other people or even yourself stop you â¤ï¸

guys, this all came from people within the native community. my own people throwing stones at me. when you know who you are you donâ€™t have to be liked. so i kept going and i stand today a motivational speaker. i wanted to make my mark on indian country and show the youth even adults the importance of self development. 
this time last year i was a cashier. i trained people for free between working and going to school. i purchased my personal training studies on a credit card not knowing if iâ€™d even pass the test! science was my weakest subject! there were days iâ€™d sit in my car after closing up the cafe and cry. i cried about self doubts, that my dream is just so far fetched! i hesitated to quit my cafe job to open up my own business. i was so afraid in that very moment but i followed my instinct and quit anyway and it paid off!!! three days after quitting my cashier job i got a call from my tribe the yakama nation to come and host a motivational talk for the tribal school! 
i aiming to teach our girls that they are strong. my message and talks come from my life experiences. i lived on the east coast and faced racism, i am a sexual assault survivor whose trial is in favor to put my abuser behind bars (only 6% of survivors actually win in court and i know i will be one of those) and iâ€™ve been bullied a lot but i never allowed those people to have that power to stop me. 
i have worked with natives across the country showing them the path to new and healthy opportunities. my motto is â€œmake indian country healthy again!â€ i hope this gives someone out there the courage to try again. whatever it is, losing weight, confronting your toxic relationships, going to school, waking up early whatever it is try again and donâ€™t let other people or even yourself stop you â¤ï¸

text:
i was an r kelly fan for most of my life. when i began djing regularly at bars and events in 2012, i would quite often throw in a kells song or two during my sets. it felt innocuous and the overwhelmingly positive response i got from the crowd every time i played â€œignition {remix)â€ or â€œstep in the name of loveâ€ ensured that i never second-guessed myself. but as more allegations against kelly rolled in over the coming years, i began feeling more uncomfortable with playing his music during sets. i chose to rationalize this inner-conflict by promising myself that i would only occasionally play â€œignition (remix)â€, particularly giraffageâ€™s excellent remix of the song (and yes, that would make it the remix to the remix to ignition). despite the song killing 100% of the time, i knew it was wrong of me to play it. i could argue that i was simply playing to the crowd, but that's an absolute cop-out.

i deeply apologize to all of kellyâ€™s survivors for continuing to give kelly a voice when they were unable to speak for themselves. it is now abundantly clear that i can no longer enable and empower problematic artists like kelly by playing their music during my dj sets. does this mean that i need to stop playing the music of deceased legends like james brown, michael jackson, john lennon and others who were also publicly condemned for their indiscretions? honestly, i donâ€™t know the answer to that, and it will take some time to come to a concrete decision. all i know for now is that i will do everything i can to support the #muterkelly and #metoo movements. i made this t-shirt to remind myself not to empower problematic artists like kelly during my dj sets.

you can read the full blog post on our website. link in bio.

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking â€˜ugh. totally uglyâ€™ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a real talk every parent should have with their son, when the â€œurgesâ€ begin! i do recommend knitting, if you canâ€™t keep your hands to yourself- haha!
yep, we are long ways from where we started about a year and a half ago, when treating womenâ€™s bodies as things you can freely touch, look up and down and discuss, was just a common practice, but we still have a long way to go. i personally have felt a tremendous shift for the better, as men are almost afraid to look like they might be abusing their powerâ€¦good! thank you to everyone who was brave enough to talk about this. iâ€™ve been known to kick a guy in the balls or punch him in the face, if he grabbed me or any of my friends inappropriately, as my sense of pride and whatâ€™s wrong and right is dominant and i get furious, if someone threatens it. iâ€™ve been on a studioâ€™s â€œblack listâ€ as i refused to date a certain exec, i donâ€™t flirt to get ahead, i donâ€™t â€œplay the gameâ€ or date people to help my careerâ€¦iâ€™m sure my career suffered from it, but hey, my soul thrives! iâ€™d gladly end up on the street and â€œnever work againâ€ in this town, if it means i get to keep my integrity, that being said- i donâ€™t have kids to feed and iâ€™m a total, trained survivor, always having been mature beyond my age, with a loving family always supporting my every decision. some women were not this lucky...some women are not in a position of choice and we should keep fighting, so they never have to chose or feel scared! letâ€™s keep the conversation going, but letâ€™s try to keep it light as much as possible! the worlds needs more laughter to heal:-) â€¢

text:
- what we worked on was ... data harvesting programs where we would pull data from users of apps and all of their friend networks and run that data through algorithms that could profile their personality traits and other psychological attributes, wylie told cnnâ€™s don lemon monday evening.

wylie said the ultimate goal was to obtain information in order to exploit mental vulnerabilities that our algorithms showed that [facebook users] had.

in addition to wylie and cambridge analytica, accounts of cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, strategic communication laboratories, and those of a university of cambridge psychologist aleksandr kogan were also suspended.

the accounts were suspended because facebook received reports that data that had been shared with cambridge and wylie from koganâ€™s app may not have been completely deleted. koganâ€™s app was removed in 2015 and facebook said they had been previously provided certifications that the data had been deleted. - several days ago, we received reports that, contrary to the certifications we were given, not all data was deleted, facebook said friday. - we are moving aggressively to determine the accuracy of these claims. if true, this is another unacceptable violation of trust and the commitments they made. we are suspending scl/cambridge analytica, wylie and kogan from facebook, pending further information.

special counsel robert mueller asked cambridge analytica last fall to surrender emails from any of its employees who worked for the trump campaign, the wall street journal reported in december. the firm complied to the request.

diana stancy correll
washington examiner

text:
music journalist #toureneblett  has been put on blast after a makeup artist stepped forward to accuse him of workplace sexual harassment back in 2017 .
tour'e who famously asked #rkelly if he liked teenage girls during a 2008 #bet interview , appeared on the clubhouse with mouse jones podcast to discuss the #survivingrkelly  docuseries and the aftermath it created .

in the comment section of the show instagram page , the makeup artist described in detail how tour'e harassed her.

#essencemagazine spoke to the victim exclusively and published the screenshots
tour'e has since issued a formal statement on response to the shocking allegations.

dani claimed to have been sent an apology via ig
which she shared with essence. what  made dani  report tour'e to his employer after she quit ??
what prompted her to blast him ??
she said it was because he was doing media appearances taking about #harveyweinstein
and his allegations of sexual misconduct. "i accepted his apology and was ok to move on but you can't be a sexual predator and go around shaming other predators ", she said 
#metoo #sexualharasment #sisterssippingthetea

.

.
my book isn't just about men and being a miserable fuck.  it's about creating an honest dialogue.  about love, life, and relationships, and building trust.  again.  itâ€™s about humanizing ourselves.

.

text:
call for proposals: 2019 season!

the public school los angeles is a space for radical communal self-education. anyone can propose a class, talk, reading group, film screening, workshop, skillshare, etc. â€“ and use our space for free! all classes and events must be open to the general public and consistent with maintaining a safer space (anti-racist, anti-sexist, anti-homo/transphobic). the public school is now seeking proposals for our 2019 season. please send your proposal to: thepublicschoolla@gmail.com. or message our instagram or facebook pages.

in your message / email, please indicate the scope of your proposed class/event (for example: recurring reading group, one-day event, series with a fixed duration). the public school is located at 951 chung king rd, los angeles.

the public school los angeles is unaffiliated with any party, political organization, or union. please disclose any political affiliations in your proposal. although we welcome classes and events hosted by organized groups, all programs must be open to the general public, and we do not host either recruitment events or internal group meetings.

we welcome all topics, but are particularly interested in proposals touching on the following themes (continued in comment section):

text:
in 2014, steve bannon â€“ then executive chairman of the â€œalt-rightâ€ news network breitbart â€“ was christopher wylieâ€™s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analyticaâ€™s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology â€“ â€œinformation operationsâ€ â€“ then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - itâ€™s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? itâ€™s like nixon on steroids.

his brief ranged across the scl group â€“ the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as â€œmi6 for hireâ€, and iâ€™d never quite understood it. - itâ€™s like dirty mi6 because youâ€™re not constrained. thereâ€™s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. itâ€™s normal for a â€˜market research companyâ€™ to amass data on domestic populations. and if youâ€™re working in some country and thereâ€™s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well thatâ€™s just a bonus.

when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though itâ€™s one he can back up with an email about howÂ mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, â€˜oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.'
.
carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text_retweet:
repost from @melissa_hartwig 
i can attest to this being one hundred percent true! 
my work performance has been so much better since getting sober and being open about it with my management and coworkers. 
i work in large corporate enterprise software sales and it's incredibly challenging, technical and full of drinking events. 
drinking was always encouraged, free and excessive for my entire career. i never paid for any of it with my own money but rather i paid with my mental and physical health. my start up was headquartered in hoboken, the city with the most bars i believe so there were many fun nights drinking with my company around hoboken and nyc and many hangovers the following morning. 
without alcohol i am more focused, more innovative, more creative and more efficient. 
one year after returning from treatment i was finally promoted to senior technical sales engineer.  this title and promotion was not given to me in the past because of a lack of confidence and confidence is the most important part of the sale. 
removing alcohol is the single most important thing i have done for my career. i would probably be fired at this point had i continued but even if i had just quit at home or something i don't think it would have been as impactful. 
my therapist in treatment helped me understand why i was not being promoted and that's its ok to be confident, it's ok to be paid what you are worth and he helped me understand that i just needed to be myself and my experience and enthusiasm for my solutions come through.  in the past i felt i wasn't smart enough or good at sales because i was so technical but i was totally wrong.  it's so wonderful to have used this to excel in my professional life. so many people told me it would be limiting to my career but they were wrong. my coworkers are incredibly supportive and some have even tried sobriety for themselves and their sales have increased!!!
#soberissexy #soberyogi #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #sobersales #sales

cambridge analyticaâ€™s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - itâ€™s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? itâ€™s like nixon on steroids.

his brief ranged across the scl group â€“ the british government has paid scl to conduct counter-extremism operations in the middle east, and the us department of defense has contracted it to work in afghanistan.

i tell him that another former employee described the firm as â€œmi6 for hireâ€, and iâ€™d never quite understood it. - itâ€™s like dirty mi6 because youâ€™re not constrained. thereâ€™s no having to go to a judge to apply for permission. itâ€™s normal for a â€˜market research companyâ€™ to amass data on domestic populations. and if youâ€™re working in some country and thereâ€™s an auxiliary benefit to a current client with aligned interests, well thatâ€™s just a bonus.

when i ask how bannon even found scl, wylie tells me what sounds like a tall tale, though itâ€™s one he can back up with an email about howÂ mark block, a veteran republican strategist, happened to sit next to a cyberwarfare expert for the us air force on a plane. - and the cyberwarfare guy is like, â€˜oh, you should meet scl. they do cyberwarfare for elections.'

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text: being the daughter of a rapist is part of what made me a feminist. i was not conceived in rape but my dad did rape my mother multiple times over the course of my childhood. a few weeks ago my mom told me that she never reported it because she didnâ€™t think anyone would believe that her husband was raping her. when i was 16 my dad had tried to have sex with/seduce my best friend. this caused irreparable damage to my relationship with my father and it was never the same. now my dadâ€™s urn sits on a shelf in my home with his picture next to it. when i look at the pictures, i see my dad but there is a part of me that sees a rapist, and sees the harm that he caused to so many women that i will never know. i am keeping my ex husbands last name as a way to disconnect that part of me from him. he will always be my dad, he bought me barbies and let me brush his long hair. my dad loved me. but i will not be his legacy.  #thequeermom #momsofslc #slcmoms #momblog #personalblog #feminist #feministissues #woman #rapesurvivor #women #yesallwomen #metoo #mom #boymom #blogging #slc #selfie #raw #personal

text:
today is human trafficking awareness day, and we urge you to take this day as an opportunity to reflect on how you can effect change.

with the recent clemency for cyntoia brown, 2019 has started off with so much hope and promise. the voices of survivors, the fearlessness of advocates and the tenacity of our allies have been the pillars behind moving the needle closer towards eradicating the commercial sexual exploitation of children. .
.
while there has been progress in language usage and laws to protect our girls, such as the safe harbor act, today so many black and brown girls in our own communities are still being commercially sexually exploited, so many still getting abused at the hands of exploiters, and so many who are still not being believed. .
.
it is not enough to believe and agree in silence. it is our responsibility to care and do something to stop the harming of our girls and young women. 
there are so many ways to get involved - if you want change, you have to act. join the fight to end #csec and empower #girls and young #women to live healthy, independent lives, free of exploitation. -
â€”
-

in continuing support of the multi-faceted output of layet johnsonâ€™s practice, good weather has parlayed an invitation from the front member tom friel to present an exhibition into an opportunity to focus on johnsonâ€™s curatorial work. while teaching and directing the galleries at central connecticut state university (ccsu), johnson has activated a devolutionary role as a curator beside an ongoing interest in comics through the lens of his drawing and conceptual art practice.
.
exemplifying this modality is the exhibitionÂ sex, death, and visceral honesty: artworks and publications by independent womenâ€™s comic artists from the 1960s underground movement to today, co-curated with leela corman. for this exhibition, corman and johnson employed an invitational method where participating artists invited further artists to join the exhibition, creating an expansive network of american womenâ€™s comic artists. for johnson, the exhibition was underlined by a personal inquiry into examining the history of womenâ€™s comics from the perspective of the contemporary.
.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
the battle of the sexes in today is unlike what it was a decade back. i could go on about the history of gender oppression, but i would like to weigh in at a certain point. competition drives evolution. we would still be jamming a cassette tape in our walkman (if you know what that is), instead of chilling with our ipods today. competition is good. but only to a point where competition isn't unhealthy. 
men have been overtaking women in most pursuits ever since time exists. it is an unsaid truth. i don't say it with a glint of pride in my voice. in the past two decades however, women have clawed back their rightful position in society. shows, movies and the stories of women being empowered are everywhere there are many unmentioned women who fight everyday to prove this point right.  with the #metoo movement, which exposes the cases of sexual harassment against women, a burgeoning number of men have been subdued and brought to justice. all is wellâ€¦ or is it?
since a couple of weeks, i have been observing posts about feminism, and also countless memes. some are inspiring, but some are making me wonder about the movementâ€™s true purpose of existence.
as of today, i feel it has now become a community to rather spread all thatâ€™s bad about men. i understand that some actions of the men are unforgivable.
but defaming, or posting humour at their expense, being a judgemental mind towards the entire race of them; youâ€™re doing the same thing that men are doing â€“ â€œmen and women are essentially part of the same hypocrisyâ€

there is no point in having feminism protests, when many women are essentially getting back at men, with the same tactics. it is not justice, it is revenge.
if women feel bad about being oppressed in some way or the other, isnâ€™t it natural that men might feel the same way, seeing such opposing stuff against them? this will be a never ending cycle, with no winner but a lots losers.

we need humane or humanism, not simply feminism.

women deserve to be empowered, but not by putting their fellow men down. the human race strives best together. so stop the judgments and pity about either gender.

god created us to coexist â€“ not to be gender extremists.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
throwback
collaboration with joef
free healthcare program at s.a. aiyeyemi primary healthcare centre.  there was massive turnout of people to access quality healthcare. this was to compliment the effort of the government in driving quality healthcare.
18th of may won't be forgotten at ilasan jakande community as s. a aiyeyemi primary health centre of eti osa lga as it was the first of its kind in jakande community. we had lots of medical practitioners in attendance and health workers. among the medical practitioners was dr. sam oyegbile the medical director of peak health limited who saw countless number of patients and also successfully two emergency cases. 
personnells from nigeria police force and lagos state transport management authority within the local government were also given opportunity to meet with our medical practitioners, matrons and pharmacists who dispensed drugs to patients as prescribed by the specialist. the team of dentists and opticians offered free dental care and eye care including dispensing of recommended glasses to those with sight defect likewise various screening were done ranging  from diabetes, malaria, hepatitis, bloodpressure, temprature etc.
there was sensitization of community on air pollution, high blood pressure, diabetes, malaria control and personal hygiene, oral hygiene etc. by the medical personnel.

beneficiaries expressed great joy as they have never experienced such in jakande community 
a big thanks to all our individual and corporate sponsors who made the program a huge success.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
two years ago i woke up on my bathroom floor and threw up again and decided it was time to stop. 
the picture on the left was me that night, drinking alone for no reason other than loneliness and slowly killing myself and losing the life i had worked hard for. 
in november 2016 i missed an important presentation because of drinking yet i didn't stop. i didn't want to be sober during the holidays so i settled on jan 1 2017 to try a year sober and by jan 11th i realized that i was incapable of stopping despite putting all my effort into it and admitted to my therapist i needed help. 
much to my surprise he suggested in patient treatment and told me i was seriously addicted to alcohol and it would only get worse. he is 50 years sober and has worked with addiction for many years and his opinion weighed heavily on me. 
he told me that i would do best at @passagesmalibu because of the holistic approach to sobriety and that the 12 step treatment centers would not help me at all. 
i called that day to see if my insurance was accepted and much to my surprise it was. 
i told my friends and family members, my management on jan 11 that i would be getting treatment and then my life changed forever. 
don't listen to anyone who says treatment doesn't work. listen to your own voice and remember that you are capable of healing. 
today i am 70 pounds lighter, debt free and have really very very little anxiety and stress. i have been given the gift of a lifetime, to be comfortable and confident in my own skin.  since i left treatment i have no desire to drink and am forever grateful for the care i received. 
had i listened to everyone in my life except for my therapist and my brother i would still be slowly killing myself. 
let's end the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse and change the way we view and treat addiction so everyone can get help when they need it. if you fail dry january it's ok but for some it could be a sign that you need help with alcohol addiction 
#soberissexy #soberyogi #transformation #empoweringwomen #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #recoveroutloud #sober

text:
one frequently asked question of the pacific rim movies is what happened to raleigh. the dashing hero of pacific rim (2013) was not even mentioned in the sequel to the befuddlement of many. the answer to his absence is made very clear when one considers the ingenious foreshadowing of his fate by the first movie. raleigh becket was convicted of sexual assault. the barrage of shirtless scenes of him is not only to keep girls and gays awake, but to highlight his sexual promiscuity, to lure them in. the second clue lies in the very first few minutes of the first film, when raleigh is shown to have no regard for authority or commands. a no means yes mentality. factor this in with the unwillingness of any character to mention the main character in uprising (2018) and it becomes abundantly clear that raleigh becket was behind bars at the time.

text:
there's nothing wrong with your willpower, trust me.

it is the diet, just like you suspected.

i'll tell you why.

diets make money from you failing.

companies like weight watchers and slimming world make money when you keep coming back.

it struck me hardest when my grandmother's friend proudly announced she had been a member of weight watchers since 1997. (they don't put that on their adverts, do they?) but here's the good news.

you don't need a diet.

you just need a better relationship with food.

because when you stop restricting yourself and start tuning into your body you'll not only feel healthier, you'll also be more confident.

see, i know that if you're looking after your body and fueling it how it wants to be, you will begin to love it.

and then you'll respect it and give it what it wants.

which means it will love you back.

how do i know?

because i've helped over 100 ladies ditch the diets and tune into their body.

i've helped them go from rating their relationship with their bodies from a 2 or 3 to an 8 and 9 out of 10.

how?

we break the cycle.

we stop the restriction 
we begin to appreciate. <3 x

text:
this is a picture of me from almost 10 years ago. most see me as a boring, stick-in-the-mud who doesn't party or even like to go out. so i went on a search for a picture of my former self after watching the r.kelly documentary and lady gagaâ€™s comments that are coming under criticism. 
i've said this once, and i'll say it again, if you haven't walked in a sexual assault/abuse  survivorâ€™s shoes, then you have no understanding of how certain victims respond to trauma or why they tend to stay in the abusive cycle. 
one thing all survivors have in common is the shame that comes with sexual assault/abuse. some hide their shame under an armor of weight gain, an overly muscular/masculine physique, or a look that is sexually suggestive and risque.  i took on all three of these personas when i was in my darkest place. 
so that brings me back to the r.kelly documentary and lady gagaâ€™s comments about recording the song â€do what u want (with my body)â€ during a dark time in her life. i knew in my gut that lady gaga had been sexually assaulted years before she spoke out about it. i knew because of all of the masks she used to wear and how open she was with her sexuality...just like i was.  putting my sexuality on display was a way for me to justify to the world (and myself) all of the horrific things that happened to me. especially those people that seemed so â€œcleanâ€ and â€œperfect.â€ itâ€™s also no coincidence that i used to dance to r. kellyâ€™s music as well as having my own messed up experience with a pop star, a story iâ€™ll save for my upcoming book. 
so my point with all this?? itâ€™s time to stop blaming and questioning  the victims of sexual assault and lumping them into male-hating, â€œme tooâ€ groups. itâ€™s time to listen to all victims regardless of their color and socio-economic backgrounds. itâ€™s time to hold these abusers/perpetrators accountable-especially public figures and celebrities like r.kelly (stop buying r. kellyâ€™s music!!! ) 
i believe r.kellyâ€™s victims and 
i will continue to make it my lifeâ€™s work to stand up for all victims and survivors of sexual assault/abuse.

i was a resident in the gems til and enrolled in educational initiative. on the day i registered for college, i brought my caseworker with me. she took a "first day of school" picture of me, smiling, under the college archway. i just passed all of my classes for my first semester. â€”
â€”
.
.
.
.

text:
they misbehave... we taxpayers get stuck holding the bill ğŸ˜  whatâ€™s up with that ugly tie? â€¢
â€¢
the #california state senate paid $350,000 to settle a workplace discrimination lawsuit filed by a former employee who alleged that the upper house failed to accommodate her emotional disabilities and fired her in retaliation after she claimed that she was sexually assaulted by an assembly staff member.

the payout to a former legislative aide to state sen. bob wieckowski (d-fremont) is one of the largest settlements the state legislature has negotiated in recent history. the senate paid the six-figure sum from its operating budget, which is funded by taxpayer dollars.

among other six-figure payouts, the senate spent $117,200 in 1998 to settle a complaint against former sen. richard polanco of los angeles, who was accused of retaliating against a former staff member who allegedly rejected his romantic advances. at the time, polanco, a democrat, declined to discuss the case.

the senate also paid $120,000 in 2010 to a staff member of former sen. roderick wright (d-inglewood) who accused the legislator of sexual harassment. wright declined to comment on the allegations at the time.

the assembly settled a lawsuit for $100,000 in 2017 after an employee alleged that former assemblyman steve fox (d-palmdale) exposed himself to her. the house also paid $110,000 in 2015 to a different staffer who alleged that fox sexually harassed her and didnâ€™t compensate her for overtime and campaign work. fox denied both allegations.. - latimes article â€¢
#metoo

text: look who was featured in rainnâ€™a speakers bureau newsletter. â¤ï¸ -  what inspired me to write this book was twofold. as a survivor, this is a sentiment that has been inside me all my life. but it wasnâ€™t until i had my own children and began observing other children coupled with the public and political events of the last couple of years (#metoo and others) that i truly felt compelled to finally get this on paper. i wanted to write a story that was approachable by all ages and that was fun and heartfelt. a story that would spark a conversation among families but most of all i wanted to give little girls and boys some language and a voice to express their feelings in situations where they might otherwise not feel compelled to do so. if i could get a child to feel comfortable and confident enough to tell the people they love when they donâ€™t feel like hugging, what potential does this carry when something comes their way from somebody that is truly unwanted? if we can empower kids earlier, make love truly unconditional, maybe we can make some noise and continue to break through those areas of silence.

text_retweet:
another 2017 #throwbackart piece while iâ€™m still busy and simultaneously recovering from still being sick.
this was an especially personal piece that i opened up about in my art blog. i havenâ€™t had time to focus on more than one artistic endeavor in the past year though (so drawing/painting of course takes the priority cake) so i took the blog link down. on top of that, iâ€™ve learned so much more about my sexual/narcissistic abuse case i experienced in 8th grade that, while this art piece still rings in as a very vulnerable and fragile part of me, there is so much more iâ€™ve been enlightened on of what i truly went through. the depravity goes a lot deeper than i ever thought and itâ€™s difficult for me to learn about or face since it triggers so many panic attacks in me. and iâ€™m learning just how many memories my mind blocked, given that the most seemingly insignificant things trip my wire and set me off; things i never remembered until iâ€™ve seen it or heard it again. on the flip side, i know itâ€™s high time for me to heal from this event and stop allowing it to control my life and my actions towards others who have nothing to do with these people. i know it doesnâ€™t stop my abusers from sleeping peacefully at night, so itâ€™s time it stopped robbing me of my own peace. i think i will always have apprehension that my abusers will resurface and claim that they knew me, loved me, or even accuse me of doing to them what they actually did to me (i put nothing above them, knowing now just how twisted and evil they were and how well they manipulated me), but iâ€™m not the same girl i was, iâ€™m not twelve/thirteen anymore. iâ€™m no longer satisfied to keep their secrets or to help them in remaining silent. i still suffer to this day for their misdeeds; i should not have to suffer in silence any longer.
-
-

text:
sometimes i don't want to get better . i wants to wrap myself in the familiar blanket of grey and mental illness. i wants to brew tea with these bags under my eyes, and enjoy the feeling of knowing the next step of my mental breakdown. i wants to paint my body red and finally be something beautiful to look out. you see - recovery isn't an instagram hashtag. recovery isn't green tea and avocado on toast with chia seeds. recovery isn't before and after picture, sponsorships, and sunday yoga. recovery is crying before class, and then going anyway - because your therapist reminded you that you just cannot let your mental illness ruin every part of your life. recovery is looking at your scars longingly, missing the feeling of breathing easy for just a minute. recovery is telling them that you're doing well, because no one wants to hear about your sadness for umpteenth time. recovery is forcing yourself to go the gym in the morning, because that's what "good" mentally  ill people do, right? because you can't recover without looking beautiful, right? it's actually about health, though, right? it's not about the fact that no one wants to listen to you if you're not easy on eyes. so i guess that this isn't actually recovery either. honestly, i don't know what recovery is, but i do know that it's been six months since i've last sucked on ice cubes for dinner; it's been one month since i've added new tally marks to the scoreboard i'm keeping on my arm. 
so yeah, i don't want to get better, but i do it anyway, because that's what recovery is - never giving up, even if it means giving up your sense of identity and having to find a new one. - better nights are to come, i hope.
.
.
.
ananya sharma.
(@afflictionwrites)
.
.
.

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
yearly, film critic rajeev masand hosts a round table celebrating the top actors and actresses in the hindi film industry. this year at the actresses round table featured the talented deepika padukone, aalia bhatt, anushka sharma, tabu, tapsee pannu and rani mukherji; whom in the last year took part in some of the greatest cinema.

amongst the topics discussed for the day were acting, politics in cinema, female struggles in the industry and the #metoo movement that in the last year brought a lot of the sexual abuse in the industry to the forefront. 
to my displeasure a senior actress; rani mukherji managed to bring in a deeply antiquated and very much so patriarchal view in and here iâ€™m loosely quoting because i refuse to subject myself to such vile opinions again, said that females in the industry who face sexual abuse or such encounter should slap the person or kick them between the legs. oh rani you will never be the champion of feminism that we need as you do not understand the complexities that every situation is different as well as behind the security guarded exterior of your bungalow that your statement is easier said than done. as a macho feminist (man who is a feminist) i can tell you that many women who find themselves in these situations are often in shock and do not know what to do or are sometimes are not powerful enough. raniâ€™s statements also lead us down a path where women who experience the abuse are unable to come out as well because they are ashamed that they could not do anything to help themselves in the moment. 
as a woman who is done so many great roles such as black, buntu aur babli and  no one killed jessica where these were strong female characters but also examined the complexity of living in the indian society, iâ€™m not sure whether rani has examined what it means to be a woman in this world of increasing violence towards women.

kudos to deepika, aalia and anushka who stood up for all women out there! 
iâ€™d like to end this post by saying that this is not to bash or shamelessly increase followers but to express an opinion, it might not be yours but it is mine.

kind regards 
south african desiâ€™s @themachofeminist_za

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
another glamour shot with my beautiful best friend. iâ€™m supposed to be the male figure and hannah is the damsel in distress. this photo was supposed to represent how, back then, a womanâ€™s life was never truly her own. the way hannah is dressed, the way iâ€™m looking at her and touching her as if i control her every move and the way she refuses to look at me with an unhappy face. itâ€™s a perfect time to post this photo to let all women know that only you have power over yourself. the times for women are changing and iâ€™m so grateful to be a part of history! with the #metoo movement, #timesup, but more importantly, a record breaking number of women running for office and especially our newly elected officials who made history this election! deb haaland and sharice davids are the first native american women elected to congress. rashida tlaib and ilhan omar are the first muslim women set to represent their states in the house. alexandria ocasio-cortez and abby finkenauer are due to be the youngest women to serve as lawmakers. kyrsten sinema became the first openly bisexual senator and the first female senator from arizona. ayanna pressley became the first black congresswoman from massachusetts. thatâ€™s just the tip of the iceberg; 102 women have been elected to the u.s. house, 14 women to the u.s. senate and 9 women will serve as governor. women didnâ€™t just contribute to the blue wave; they fueled it! 
as a woman, itâ€™s time to tap into your full potential! if youâ€™re a woman and youâ€™re reading this, know that youâ€™re a diamond! nothing left to do but to shine on â€œlike the moon and stars and the sun!â€ #womenruletheworld #girlpower #womenmadehistory #womensenators #womengovernors #womenlawmakers #youareincontrol #anythingispossible #womensupportwomen #empowerment #yeswecan #bestfriendsforever #bff #sistertribe #supermodels #glamourshot #passion #power #pretty #potential #youreadiamond  #shineon #likethemoonandthestarsandthesun

the most powerful truth we need to know about our doubts, fears and failures, is that weâ€™re not alone. others are struggling too.

text:
dealing with prospective tenants i am ready to tell my story!

good morning, 
soooo i am not exactly sure of the reason some prefer to work with realtors in regard to rentals. however, i will like to clear some things up that i honestly don't feel "some" realtors may be explaining to tenants clearly or maybe tenants have selective hearing idk.ğŸ˜’ here we go *clears throat*

many properties that realtors have access to are privately owned or managed by an hoa. therefore, landlords are able to make their own rules such as income, credit and bkgd requirements versus apartment complexes tend to be a little more flexible and will allow lower credit scores, extra security deposit if credit isn't up to par, and accept no bkgd within 10 years etc. 
with that being said if you know you don't meet these requirements it is likely you will not qualify for rentals that realtors have access to and/or you will lose your application fees. you can either work on meeting the requirements below or focus on selecting a property with an apartment complex.

typical rental property requirements âœ”ï¸620+ credit score (i've seen higher)
âœ”ï¸income 3x the rental amount
âœ”ï¸no bkgd, no evictions
âœ”ï¸1st, last and security deposit 
now i don't know who you are, i dont know necessarily what you are looking for but if you are looking for a rental with bad credit i can tell you i am not a magician i will require you to provide a copy of all 3 reports and proof of income. if you don't have them i have a  particular set of skills...skills  that will allow me to pull your credit reports..all 3 for a whopping $1!! skills that i have acquired over a  very long career as the  ceo of apex credit consultants. skills that make dreams come true for people with bad credit. if you have decent credit i can place you in a rental. if you donâ€™t and are looking for a rental i will not help you find one, i will offer your credit repair and that will be the end of it. i will not look for rentals for you, you will give me your bad credit and i will fix it!

sidenote: you can purchase a home with 580, evictions, bkgd and sometimes little or no money down but who am i to tell you to be an overachieverğŸ’
name: Kera B. | Real Estate + Credit

text:
thank you friend! wise words!
@authenticintimacy @julislattery ãƒ»ãƒ»ãƒ»
have you heard the conversions around r kelly and the new documentary summarizing his sexual abuse? #survivingrkelly
.
we can all agree that we hate the evil represented by what r. kelly has done to so many women. however, we often yawn at the evil that opens the door to sexual violation and exploitation. just a few years ago, how many of us flocked to read or watch fifty shades of grey, a sexually explicit romance story involving a â€œred room of painâ€ and bdsm? our culture (including the christian culture) has conceded the territory of sexuality to worldly, secular thought.
.
letâ€™s remember that satan himself is the prince of this world, yet he disguises himself as an angel of light. when we kick god out of our sex lives, we essentially give that ground to evil. encouraging just a little bit of pornography or hooking up sets us up for the mentality that we can have, therefore should take, whatever our lust desires.
.
you might think itâ€™s a stretch to link seemingly benign acts like casual sex and porn to what is documented in surviving r. kelly, but evil takes ground with seemingly small concessions. itâ€™s far more acceptable to lament the abusive result of the #metoo movement than it is to teach sexual morality. yet the two are forever intertwined. itâ€™s not enough to compassionately care about victims. we must also confront the compromises we make that give satan power in our lives. when we elevate humanity as our own moral authority, evil will win.
- dr. juli slattery
.

text:
i know the smiley, filtered selfies get more attention and maybe that is proof of the deeper issue. everyone finds life and people are more â€œlikableâ€ as long as the dirty truths are hidden. 
we prefer filters over truth, scripted reality...but why?  why does my shame make you more uncomfortable than the person who stained my soul? 
life would be more palatable if we embraced those that need us to listen. 
in the wake of #survivingrkelley #metoo #weinstein #cosby #kevinspacey #mattlauer we need to remember that women, children, boys, girls and men are traumatized everyday. lives altered and no one to tell them itâ€™s ok to speak.  my hope is that everyone can have a voice and be heard.  that every time someone speaks out, another person will feel #empowered to do the same. that #girlstoo will learn they have an ally and that the experiences of those that come before them can make a safer passage for their future.  we are not dirty, we are not liars, we are not being dramatic or looking for attention. no ones pain or suffering greater than another, no story more valid than the next. 
we are #survivors.

text:
a few years ago i made the biggest change ever in my life by deciding to break free from a toxic relationship that was killing me physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually. since then,  i've had to adjust and survive as a single mother of three along with juggling day to day obstacles. but, i learned how to make it work and have been living a happier and healthier life since. now, i'm no stranger to overcoming challenges and leaving a toxic relationship was just one of the many struggles i've had to overcome. ***
join on january 16 @ 7pm est for my free webinar (linktree in bio to sign up) where we will discuss the tools and resources i used to walk away from a toxic relationship, become a published author, and begin the journey to creating the life i always wanted. the first five people to sign up will receive a free copy of my book let mia tell it and everyone will receive my 30 day breaking toxic cycles journal for free! ***
i can't wait to grow and elevate with you and assist you with breaking the cycles that has been holding you back and keeping you from living your best life! *select the linktree in my bio to sign up!

"[girls] get stuff done because we know no one else will do it for us...girls resist because we care, because we're mad, because we're smart, and because we're powerful."
ğŸ‘ğŸ‘ğŸ‘
so you say you want a revolution? this book is literally your guide. guys, when i got this book from @quirkbooks (thank you!), i knew i was going to love it. a book encouraging girls to use their voices and stand up for what they believe in? i'm down.ğŸ’ªbut i didn't realize this would be a literal guide to the revolution. it's kind of incredible.  this isn't just a book that says inspires you and says "go for it!", it tells you how.
ğŸ¤¯
first, the book gives you information. information on power structure, gender bias, the wage gap, rape culture, lack of women in government. then it helps you find your cause. once you're ready to go, this book walks you through everything from fundraising, lobbying and marketing to running an effective meeting and creating the perfect phonebank.  finding yourself up against people who disagree?  this book will help you handle that. starting to burn out? flip to chapter 8.
ğŸ™Œ
you could literally use this book to organize the women's march (seriously, i think you could), but you can also use it to make change in smaller ways. the book is inclusive, informational, inspirational and, most importantly, instructional. it is super.

text:
the new york times

the woman who created #metoo long before hashtags

tarana burke created a nonprofit organization to help victims of sexual harassment and assault.creditvia justbeinc.org

byÂ sandra e. garcia

oct. 20, 2017

in 1997, #taranaburke sat across from a 13-year-old girl who had been sexually abused. the young girl was explaining her experience, and it left ms. burke speechless. that moment is where the me too campaign was born. â€œi didnâ€™t have a response or a way to help her in that moment, and i couldnâ€™t even say â€˜me too,â€™ â€ ms. burke said. â€œit really bothered me, and it sat in my spirit for a long time,â€ she added.

ten years after that conversation, ms. burke created just be inc., a nonprofit organization that helps victims of sexual harassment and assault. she sought out the resources that she had not found readily available to her 10 years before and committed herself to being there for people who had been abused.

and she gave her movement a name: #metoo.

on sunday, those two words burst into the spotlight of social media with #metoo, a hashtag promoted by the actress alyssa milano. amid the firestorm that ignited, some women of color noted pointedly that the longtime effort by ms. burke, who is black, had not received support over the years from prominent white feminists.

ms. milano was seeking to give a voice to sexual abuse victims, after accusations of sexual harassment and assault were leveled against the hollywood producer harvey weinstein.

ms. burke created the â€œme tooâ€ campaign in 2007.creditwww.justbeinc.org

after her tweet, social mediaÂ was soon flooded with stories of harassment and assault, as #metoo became a way for users to tell their experience with sexual violence and stand in solidarity with other survivors. the hashtag was widely used on twitter, facebook, snapchat and other platforms; on facebook, it was shared in more than 12 million posts and reactions in the first 24 hours,Â according to the associated press.

it was a particularly combustible moment for social media activism. days earlier, amid the allegations against mr. wein
